Federal lawmakers from Kano State have shown their solidarity with the state government through individual donations to the state’s Fund Raising Committee on COVID-19, which was inaugurated by Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje. A press statement issued by the commissioner for Information and member of the committee, Malam Muhammad Garba, indicated that Senator representing Kano North, Barau Jibrin, donated the sum of N4million, while Senators Ibrahim Shekarau and Kabiru Gaya representing Kano Central and Kano South respectively offered N2 million each. In the same vein, the House Leader at the Green Chamber, Hon. Alhassan Ado Doguwa and 10 other members donated N1million each. The members are Hon. Kabiru Alhassan Rurum, Hon. Mustapha Bala Dawaki, Hon. Nasir Ali Ahmed, Hon Tijjani Abdulkadir Jobe, Hon. Munir Babba Dan’Agundi, Hon. Abdullahi Mahmud Gaya, Hon Abubakar Jibrin Bichi, Hon. Sha’aban Ibrahim Sharada, Hon. Aminu Suleiman Goro, and Hon. Hafizu Sani. Malam Garba also announced that 13 other members of the House of Representatives collectively made a donation of N3.250million. He said the director- general, National Civil Aviation Authority (NCCA), Musa Nuhu Shu’aibu, contributed N1million. The commissioner said that anyone willing to donate to the committee in cash should pay/transfer to this account: Kano State COVID-19 Support, UBA, Account No: 1022751785.